documents.product_title: Sega Hatsune Miku: Project Diva Extend for PSP (Japanese Language Import)
documents.review_text: Im a big Hatsune MIku fan and when i saw this at a cheap price i tapped the order button just to get it! two weeks later (i think) it came in the mail and i opened it and put it in my PSP and I really love it!!! tho its in japanese i don't really care about, i still play it! hoping to learn japanese in the future so i can understand what i am doing

These are among the most nicely detailed amiibo I've seen so far.  Great use of multiple materials, that parts that should shine do and the parts that shouldn't don't.  I suspect that because the design of the characters is so simple they were more able to flesh out the details.

documents.product_title: Xbox 360 Power Base Induction Charger - Black
documents.review_text: I bought this charger around December and so far this is what I can tell you about it.  cons.   1. There's no way to tell how charged te batteries are using the xbox button in the middle of the xbox controller, when you do the bars for the battery life are always full so you won't know when the charge is going to run out.    2. The charging stand where you put the batteries on isn't designed very well for charging the batteries without them being attached to the controller, if you try and charge them without it connected to the controller you have to try and line it up just right with the little LED on the charging dock and the battery, if you don't the light showing you how charged the battery is will stay red (no/low battery power) and will never change to yellow or green (fully/high battery power), resulting in you over charging the battery. The easiest way to prevent that is to just have the battery connected to an xbox 360 controller when you charge it and it will slide right into place. (P.S. I myself might have accidentally over charged the batteries because the light indicator showing how charged the battery is will only go to yellow. I'm not sure if this was caused by me or if the batteries themselves were defective or something of that nature.)    3. The average time the batteries last after being charged is around 3 to 5 hours of use, which is abit shorter than other batteries but if you aren't using both of them and have a second xbox 360 controller (you can charge the batteries without them being attached to the controller, it's just harder to line them up with the charging bay!) you can pop the dead battery into there and put that on the charging bay and then rotate them when those batteries get dead. If you are using both of the battery packs at the same time however get ready for some downtime for you and your friend for the batteries to recharge.    4. The instructions that come with the "Xbox 360 Power Base Induction Charger" do not tell you how long you should charge the batteries for or how long you shouldn't charge the batteries for in case the light indicator is messed up or something. (As stated above my batteries no longer show a green light when charging and will only show a yellow one.)  Pros.   1. The batteries work, I've had them for a few months now and they still stay charged for 3-5 hours of use.    2. You can use rumble without the the xbox 360 controller turning off (I'm talking about the issue for the xbox 360 controller where when you use rumble the batteries jiggle out of place for a moment and then that turns off your xbox controller which can get really annoying for online play or playing in general. Here's a video showing you a fix for that problem in case you decide not to buy these. [...])    3. They are really light making the xbox 360 controller alot lighter (Not sure if everyone sees that as a pro, but I do.)    4. The charging dock is small and lets you charge two batteries at once and they don't have to be connected to the controller to charge (but it is harder to charge them without being connected to a controller.  I would also like to add that I do not know if the batteries automatically stop charging the batteries once the charge light turns green to prevent over charging the battery, but I it might. If anyone knows a added comment to confirm would be great.
This game is the best one yet the game play is so much better than the last one a must buy

dimensions.name: Reliability
dimensions.description: The review is considered reliable, as opposed to reporting unreliable information

mapping.label: Completely Disagree:
mapping.description: the review provides unreliable or untrustworthy information

mapping.label: Partially Disagree:
mapping.description: the review has some unreliable information

mapping.label: Neutral:
mapping.description: the review's reliability cannot be definitively determined

mapping.label: Partially Agree:
mapping.description: the review is mostly reliable

mapping.label: Completely Agree:
mapping.description: the review is entirely reliable and considered trustworthy

dimensions.name: Neutrality
dimensions.description: The review is expressed in objective terms, as opposed to resulting subjective or biased

mapping.label: Completely Disagree:
mapping.description: the review is highly subjective or biased, providing unreliable information

mapping.label: Partially Disagree:
mapping.description: the review has some elements of neutrality but also contains subjective or biased expressions

mapping.label: Neutral:
mapping.description: the neutrality of the review cannot be definitively determined

mapping.label: Partially Agree:
mapping.description: the review is mostly expressed in objective terms but may have some subjective elements

mapping.label: Completely Agree:
mapping.description: the review is entirely neutral, expressed objectively without bias

dimensions.name: Precision
dimensions.description: The review is precise/specific, as opposed to vague

mapping.label: Completely Disagree:
mapping.description: the review provides imprecise and vague information

mapping.label: Partially Disagree:
mapping.description: the review contains some imprecise details and vagueness

mapping.label: Neutral:
mapping.description: the review's precision cannot be definitively determined

mapping.label: Partially Agree:
mapping.description: the review is mostly precise, with some specific details

mapping.label: Completely Agree:
mapping.description: the review is entirely precise and considered trustworthy

dimensions.name: Completeness
dimensions.description: The review is complete as opposed to partial

mapping.label: Completely Disagree:
mapping.description: the review is deficient in crucial details, presenting an incomplete overview

mapping.label: Partially Disagree:
mapping.description: the review includes some details, but overall, it is incomplete

mapping.label: Neutral:
mapping.description: the completeness of the review cannot be definitively determined

mapping.label: Partially Agree:
mapping.description: the review is mostly complete in providing necessary details

mapping.label: Completely Agree:
mapping.description: the review provides a comprehensive overview

dimensions.name: Informativeness
dimensions.description: The review allows deriving useful information as opposed to well-known facts and/or tautologies

mapping.label: Completely Disagree:
mapping.description: the review lacks informative content, providing insufficient details

mapping.label: Partially Disagree:
mapping.description: the review has some informative elements, but overall, it is not fully detailed

mapping.label: Neutral:
mapping.description: the informativeness of the review cannot be definitively determined

mapping.label: Partially Agree:
mapping.description: the review is mostly informative, offering relevant details

mapping.label: Completely Agree:
mapping.description: the review is entirely informative, delivering a comprehensive and detailed analysis
